724473f-b.title: Manhattan: West End Avenue - 96th Street (West)
724473f-b.text:
740 West End Avenue at N.E. corner of 96th Strcet, ''The Della Robbia'',
the original building erected on the site, some time between 1910
and 1916. The Riversioe Theatre, shown on 96th Street, was built
about the same time.
The small house above it is the rather older ''Theodora'', five-story
apartment house; it will be demolished about 1930. The building
with the grocery store, shown in part on the N.W. corner opposite
The Della Robbia, was erected about 1900.
About 1920.
New York Sun Staff Photographer.
Gift of E. M. Jenks.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

724472f-a.title: Manhattan: West End Avenue - 96th Street (West)
724472f-a.text:
736 West End Avenue at S.E. corner of 96th Street, a new fireproof
building nearing completion on tho site of old 738 and 736. The
two remaining old houses shown adjoining this building on West End
Avenue are 734 and 732. Compare this with the pictures of these
houses about 1910.
About 1929.
